<TEXT>
a series of 21 photos of clouds by photographer 
alfred stieglitz brought 396000 at auction monday and a watch 
sold for 539000 both setting records auction houses said 
the watch sold to a private collector for the highest price ever 
paid for a watch at auction in the united states said sothebys 
the photo sale was a record price for a single lot of photography 
a spokeswoman for christies auction house said 
the watch with a face measuring 14 inches was made by swiss 
craftsmen and took three years to complete it was designed and 
commissioned in 1927 by james schulz who worked for tiffanys 
before opening his own business and who also designed watches for 
cartier 
it was the most complicated watch of its size ever to be 
made said daryn schnipper a watch expert for sothebys 
in addition to a standard dial that tells time the watch face 
has four smaller dials one gives the month one gives the day of 
the week one registers the date and has a second hand and another 
gives the phases of the moon 
the previous record for a watch sold at auction was set earlier 
this year when a wristwatch went for 275000 
stieglitz equivalents three series of seven each was 
bought by an anonymous collector said bethe goldberg a publicist 
for christies the series consists of 21 different blackandwhite 
photos of clouds each measuring 3 by 4 inches dating from the 
1920s 
stieglitz signed the title page of the series dedicating it to 
alma wertheim a patron and friend the series was sold by the 
wertheim family goldberg said 
