<TEXT>
thomas e slaughter a general executive on the 
headquarters staff of the associated press has been named director 
of ap newsfeatures 
slaughter succeeds dan perkes who is retiring after 32 years 
with the news cooperative 
ap newsfeatures develops and markets syndicated features and 
books including the associated press stylebook and the 
word a guide to newswriting 
ap president louis d boccardi announced the appointment on 
monday 
boccardi said that in addition to his newsfeatures duties 
slaughter will assist in development of aps strategic plan under 
vice president patrick t obrien who is director of strategic 
planning and ap treasurer 
slaughter 40 was transferred to the ap headquarters staff in 
august after four years as aps chief of bureau in seattle he went 
to seattle after five years as chief of bureau in newark nj 
he joined the ap in topeka kan in 1973 and worked in sioux 
falls sd and denver before being named correspondent in 
cheyenne wyo in 1976 he was correspondent in tallahassee fla 
and assistant chief of bureau in dallas before being named newark 
bureau chief in 1980 
slaughter is a native of salina kan and a graduate of the 
university of kansas he also holds a masters degree in business 
administration 
</TEXT>
