now a leading activist with the charter 77 human rights group it 
is still strong and monolithic in czechoslovakia but they feel 
more alone 
the conviction that change is coming has grown markedly in 
prague in the last two months buoyed by the dramatic upheaval in 
east germany the emergence of a noncommunist government in poland 
and hungarys bold moves toward democracy 
but czechoslovaks have not suffered the privations endured by 
