are legally obscene under urbana ordinances 
for example the state court said there are ads in the 
magazines showing sexual activity in which small black dots were 
used to obscure sexual organs the dots would not preclude a jury 
from finding the pictures are obscene the state court said 
the store owners said the ban violates a 1973 supreme court 
ruling that says material is obscene if the average person using 
contemporary community standards finds it appeals to prurient 
interests and depicts sexual acts in a patently offensive manner 
that ruling said the work must be judged as a whole and must be 
found to lack serious literary artistic political or scientific 
