<TEXT>
the national safety council has issued the 
following guidelines for parents and children at halloween 
childrens costumes should be large enough so that warm 
clothing can be worn underneath yet short enough so that a child 
wont trip avoid shoes that make walking difficult 
for visibility use light colors in costumes and attach 
reflective tape to them have children use reflective treat bags 
attach a small childs name address and phone number inside 
his sleeve in case he gets lost but dont openly display the 
personal information on the childs costume 
masks can obscure a childs vision use nontoxic makeup 
instead 
be sure children travel only in familiar neighborhoods and 
that they dont enter strangers homes they should follow a 
designated travel route with a definite return time and not 
trickortreat past dark give them coins to call home if any 
problems arise 
remind children not to eat any treat before its been 
inspected by a parent 
teach children pedestrian safety 
motorists should slow down in residential areas and watch for 
children 
