parliament on monday approved 
legislation granting amnesty to many people convicted of crimes 
punishable by less than three years in prison and it created an 
office to control government and party finances 
the laws to take effect in november were among several items 
on the agenda on the opening day of the legislatures first session 
since it rewrote the communist constitution to reflect democratic 
ideals 
hungarys rapidly evolving reform course has put it in the 
vanguard of democratic change within the soviet bloc along with 
poland the first warsaw pact nation with a government not 
dominated by the communists 
at its last sitting which ended oct 20 hungarys parliament 
adopted a series of laws and constitutional amendements 
establishing the legal framework for the first multiparty elections 
since the now defunct communist party consolidated power in 1948 
the communist party formally known as the hungarian socialist 
workers party dissolved itself oct 7 at a historic congress 
that gave birth to its successor the socialist party the new 
party which professes democratic ideals retains political 
control but its leaders have promised to hand over power if 
defeated at the polls next year 
in another major move to break with the communist past acting 
president matyas szueroes proclaimed the existence of the republic 
of hungary oct 23 the 33rd anniversary of the 1956 antistalinist 
revolt 
the proclamation which formally terminated the 
communistcreated peoples republic of hungary was cheered by more 
than 100000 hungarians 
the amnesty law applies to those serving terms of three years or 
less who are in the following categories pregnant women women 
with children under 14 living with them women over 55 and men over 
60 and those suffering from terminal illness the terms are halved 
for those in these categories serving sentences exceding three 
years 
the amnesty does not apply to those facing or serving sentences 
for violent or sexual crimes 
creation of an auditors office was meant to reestablish 
impartial control over government and party spending which was 
effectively abolished after the communists took over the office 
which also has jurisdiction over the finances of state enterprises 
is responsible to parliament 
the number of legislators present to vote on the two bills 
differed accounting for the different totals 
