rejoin the un educational scientific and cultural organization 
the united states left unesco in 1984 followed by britain and 
singapore on the grounds that the parisbased un agency was 
politicized antiwestern mismanaged and too expensive 
science education culture and communications are not 
confined by national boundaries the un chief said 
international organizations which deal with questions of global 
concern such as these should be truly universal 
unesco is holding its general conference meeting in paris 
considering a reform program by its directorgeneral federico 
mayor zaragoza and a more thirdworld oriented agenda proposed by 
the agencys executive board 
