<TEXT>
air pollution reached dangerous levels in 
the capital monday because of warm calm conditions and the 
government announced emergency measures for cars and industry 
the environment ministry banned all cars with license plates 
ending in even numbers from most of athens from 7 am tuesday to 
10 am wednesday 
industries in and around athens also were ordered to limit fuel 
consumption by 30 percent during the emergency 
the independent pakoe environment agency said 273 people 
received treatment for heart and respiratory problems heightened by 
the pollution 
the weather bureau said warm calm weather would continue on 
tuesday threatening to raise pollution levels even higher 
over the years air pollution has become a serious problem 
reaching emergency levels whenever warm windless weather traps the 
thick brown smog within the mountains that circle the coastal plain 
where more than onethird of greeces 10 million people live 
in september 1982 the government banned half of the capitals 
800000 private cars from the central athens area during office 
hours vehicles are allowed into the restricted zone on alternate 
days depending on their license plate numbers 
</TEXT>
