investigating allegations of political favoritism at the department 
of housing and urban development which he headed during the reagan 
administration 
he contended that because the hearings related to his tenure at 
the department hud should pay his fees 
the department forwarded pierces request to the justice 
department for a ruling on whether the former secretary qualified 
for reimbursement under the regulations 
two weeks later the justice department replied that it had no 
responsibility to represent pierce and therefore would not rule on 
whether he qualified for reimbursement the department said it was 
up to hud whether to represent pierce or pay his fees 
its a hot potato said pierce attorney robert plotkin 
hud hands off to justice justice hands off back to hud 
plotkin said the justice department defied a plain reading of 
government regulations when it determined it wasnt responsible for 
expenses pierce incurred during the subcommittee investigation 
