marcel jansen quickly told reporters he had no official statement 
on the demonstration and they should address questions to chief 
government spokesman miroslav pavel who is on vacation 
the party newspaper said the 149 would be charged under 
antidemonstration laws passed earlier this year that impose fines 
of up to 2000 
more than 10000 people gathered saturday in pragues wenceslas 
square to mark the 71st anniversary of czechoslovak independence 
they chanted calls for free elections a new government and the 
removal of communist party leader milos jakes 
