<TEXT>
mexican singer pedro vargas nicknamed the 
tenor of the americas died early monday of heart failure his 
family said he was 85 
he died in his sleep his oldest son pedro vargas jr told 
reporters vargas had been suffering for several years from 
diabetes and heart problems 
known for his rich melodious voice vargas singing career 
spanned more than 60 years and included performances at carnegie 
hall madison square garden and the white house 
he sang for presidents franklin d roosevelt and harry s 
truman shared the stage with sammy davis jr and counted frank 
sinatra and julio iglesias among his friends and admirers 
vargas was considered one of the brightest starts in the 
golden age of mexican music which spanned the 1930s and 40s 
vargas in partnership with composer mexican agustin lara 
popularized the bolero and the paso doble the fastpaced 
spanish double footstep dance he also appeared in dozens of films 
most of them produced in mexico 
it was considered one of the greatest musical partnerships in 
the spanishspeaking world 
vargas was born in san miguel de allende in central mexico on 
april 29 1904 the second of 13 children he was a quiet and 
introverted child whose family wanted him to become a priest 
instead he developed an early vocation for music and began 
singing in a chorus in high school in mexico city in 1917 after 
high school he tried to become a bullfighter but failed and 
turned to studying medicine 
but singing remained his first love and his strong tenor voice 
gained him quick admission to the national conservatory of music 
vargas got his first break in 1928 when he was selected to sing 
the role of turidu in the italian opera cavalleria rusticana by 
pedro mascagani the performance was so successful that it led to a 
tour of the united states 
vargas then turned to popular ballads eventually reaching an 
audience of millions in latin america the united states europe 
and asia his rendition of fleurdelis was his hallmark 
throughout latin america in the 1930s 
he was a personal friend of frank sinatra and although they 
never sang together he did sing with a mutual friend sammy davis 
jr his son recalled monday 
this morning i received with great emotion condolences from 
my fathers death from frank sinatra julio iglesias and libertad 
lamarque among others pedro vargas jr said 
vargas is survived by his wife teresa campos four children and 
seven grandchildren 
</TEXT>
