foreign governments do not want to disturb chinas tentative 
orientation toward the west so carefully nurtured since the nixon 
years 
the cold war has faded and with it fears of communist excesses 
china activists suffered a sharp emotional letdown after seeing 
their hopes crushed so abruptly they recognize bleakly the 
