<TEXT>
when paula abdul was a child she dreamed of 
following in the footsteps of such singing and dancing legends as 
gene kelly fred astaire and judy garland 
today it looks as if the diminutive 26yearold vocalist and 
choreographer could be well on her way 
abduls debut album forever your girl has sold more than 2 
million copies with three no 1 singles straight up forever 
your girl and cold hearted a fourth single the way you 
love me is also burning up the charts 
to top it off she recently won three mtv awards for her music 
and videos and even more recently won an emmy for her choreography 
of the tracey ullman show 
she is understandably overwhelmed 
i feel redundant when i keep saying im overwhelmed or im 
excited but its really something you cant explain she said 
its just an inner feeling that you have you smile and you laugh 
and you think im a real lucky girl 
abdul has come a long way from her days cheerleading for the los 
angeles lakers considering it was an opportunity she almost missed 
she heard about the audition and went with her girlfriends but 
became discouraged when she saw hundreds of laker girl hopefuls 
milling about waiting for their chance to perform 
i drove the girls that were auditioning with me so i had to 
wait for them and at the very last second after hours i said 
what the heck im just gonna go ahead 
i was a big basketball fan she said i was a huge laker 
fan and we each would get two season seats what more could you 
want the lakers were really hot 
soon after being selected as one of the 12 cheerleaders in 1981 
the choreographer left to get married she asked a very young abdul 
to take over the job 
like everything she commits herself to abdul devoted herself to 
getting the laker girls noticed she incorporated traditional 
cheerleading with jazzy dance steps and savvy street moves 
the fans did notice and the offers started pouring in for 
abdul to choreograph she helped smooth out dance steps for a music 
video by the jacksons and did some commercial work then she 
choreographed the videos for janet jacksons what have you done 
for me lately and when i think of you among others 
i wasnt looking to become a choreographer really abdul 
said these were little jobs that came my way and it was 
something that was good money and it was fun 
besides choreographing videos for jackson zz top and the 
pointer sisters abdul arranged dance steps for aretha franklin 
kool and the gang and george michael concert tours 
she also choreographed two films the running man and 
coming to america she became so busy she had to say goodbye to 
the laker girls 
but with the looming examples of kelly garland and astaire 
abdul still was drawn to song 
abdul laughed as she talked recently about her break into the 
recording business she said the record company executives who 
worked with her on music videos kept asking so what do you want 
to do when you grow up paula 
she would respond i want to be an artist on your label 
finally two executives took her seriously and signed her to a 
recording deal forever your girl was the result 
i remember thinking when i was making the album look im 
having a good time doing this but it would be really wonderful if i 
really sold albums it would be wonderful if i had hit songs 
she said 
the album has since produced the three hits and probably will 
generate a few more 
you feel like well gosh i have a no 1 single thats 
really great then you have another single that comes out and it 
goes no 1 and you freak out she said i freaked out i 
couldnt believe it then you have a third one that goes no 1 and 
you go oh my god im dreaming 
abdul never expected such quick success when she was a young 
girl taking hours and hours of dancing lessons and dreaming of 
hollywood in her san fernando valley neighborhood 
her dark good looks come from a brazilian and syrian father and 
a french canadian mother she said when she was little her mother 
warned her about the perils of show business and urged her to have 
another dream 
abdul seriously took the advice and went to california state 
university northridge where she entered the radiotvfilm program 
i still had a strong love of song and dance and acting but i 
knew in case it never worked for me then i would maybe have a 
career as a sports commentator 
unfortunately for the sports world she never took that career 
track and now juggles choreography and singing while trying to 
find time for herself after a recent early morning photo shoot 
abdul admitted she was pressed for time because she had to catch a 
plane to paris 
it gets draining she said when it gets to be a little 
bit too much thats when i have to back off at least for a day 
because i dont want it ever to be tedious i want to always feel 
the way im feeling now 
she had been scheduled to choreograph the film version of the 
musical evita but got a reprieve of the fourmonth project in 
spain when meryl streep dropped out as lead with that shelved 
abdul wants to take a week off then immerse herself in a second 
album which may include some surprises 
musically im more involved now and i have different ideas of 
where i want to go she said im not going to deviate too much 
from what ive done with whats been successful for me but i plan 
on stretching a lot 
her success has not stifled her ambition she eventually wants 
to break into acting much like her hollywood idols and is 
currently considering several prospects 
i definitely want to act she said but i definitely want 
to continue making music and ill never give up choreography 
