<TEXT>
the rev marshall d moran has talked 
with mahatma ghandi and drove indias first prime minister 
jawaharlal nehru around in a jeep but to most of those who know 
him hes simply mickey mouse 
i want to continue as long as i find people wanting to talk to 
me said the 83yearold chicagoborn jesuit ham license 9n1mm 
the only private radio operator in this tiny himalayan kingdom 
sandwiched between china and india 
since he started out on the radio he built himself moran 
estimates hes talked to more than 80000 ham operators i used 
to talk to captains of ships at sea they used to respond saying 
your signal is not good 
in 1961 the maritime radio club of houston sent him the radio 
hes used since 
moran learned to make receivers from a friend in school when 
i was 13 i used to sell them to my friends the parts would cost 
me 90 i would sell it for 100 in those days 10 was good 
money 
those were also the days when broadcasting was young and no one 
had heard of television i saw the development of radio and 
television from the very beginning i was lucky to see the 
beginning 
moran set sail from the united states in 1929 in search of a 
new homeland in asia he settled first in india and became 
principal of st xaviers school in patna in the eastern indian 
province of bihar 
it was there in 1939 while i was in the middle of putting a 
high school in patna i met gandhi the great man after a half 
hour talk with him i agreed to work for him moran recalls 
in 1946 just before the end of the second world war i was 
going to shillong to give a retreat lecture before christmas he 
said and jawaharlal nehru who a year later would become prime 
minister was on the train 
nehru was then president of the congress party large crowds 
would come to see and hear him when the train stopped at railway 
stations and when his microphone did not work his voice stopped 
and i went up to the speakers and connected the wires moran 
said nehru asked me what is the name of your company which 
takes so good care of loudspeakers 
i said i am sorry i am a jesuit priest and an american 
missionary 
moran met nehru again in 1947 and drove him around bihar in his 
jeep during hindumuslim rioting before the partition of india 
two years later as principal of st xaviers in patna moran 
made his first trip to nepal to conduct examinations for patna 
university he moved to the mountain kingdom in 1951 so settle 
intent on starting a boarding school 
at the time there was no airport so he took a train to raxaul 
the last indian township on the border and made his way to 
bhimphedi at the base of the himalayan foothills there were 
eight porters waiting for me with an ulinkath an open palanquin 
four of them carried me on it and four others followed running 
behind them changing turns every 10 minutes he said 
this was the only means of transportation system in those days 
to enter into the nepalese capital i saw even cars being 
carried by men on their shoulder along the trail at bhimphedi 
people took off the wheels of a car and they put the car on top of 
two long logs with nine planks strapped sideways and 36 people in 
rows of four men carried it on the trail to thankot 
when moran brought his own car into nepal that in 1951 however 
he did it by air even so he said it was a herculean effort 
the door of the dc3 was so narrow that i had to take off the 
back and front bumpers first the car was pushed into the plane 
with barely an inch to spare to fit it in some of the planes 
hinges had to be removed and when i asked the pilot for his 
permission he said i cant give permission to do so but if i go 
and take a cup of tea i might not see it hurry up 
that year moran met nehru a third time the prime minister was 
visiting as a state guest saw me at a civic reception standing 
among the huge crowd and told king tribhuvan pointing at me this 
is my most favourite driver 
it was also the year that moran established st xaviers in an 
old maharajas summer palace 5000 feet up in the himalayan 
foothills where he still teaches five days a week when he 
doesnt have his ears on 
