miller brewing co on monday introduced its 
first nonalcoholic brew a product it said was spurred by growing 
antidrinking sentiment in the united states 
miller also announced plans for a 12week super bowl advertising 
campaign featuring two celebritycoached teams battling on a 
football field over rival taste great and less filling 
claims for miller lite beer 
millers sharps brand nonalcohol brew will be introduced for 
sale nationwide jan 1 and will be backed by a national marketing 
effort but no testmarketing miller officials said 
nonalcoholic beers have been popular in europe for some time 
and other us brewers including anheuserbusch cos inc pabst 
and g heileman already sell nonalcohol or lowalcohol brands 
miller touts sharps as having a taste like real beer due to a 
new brewing process the company developed 
miller experimented in 1984 with a lowalcohol beer also called 
sharps but the brew did not advance beyond test marketing 
annual us production of nonalcoholic beers is about a million 
barrels a year compared with the national beer market of more than 
182 million barrels but the nonalcoholic segment is growing at 
the rate of 10 percent to 15 percent a year while the overall beer 
market has been stable analysts said 
david krishock new products category director for miller said 
growth in the nonalcoholic beer market prompted miller to bring 
sharps out nationwide without test marketing 
the new brew will have 74 calories per 12ounce serving about 
half the calories of regular beer and will be sold in bottles 
cans and kegs 
jerry steinman publisher of the industry newsletter beer 
marketers insights said millers introduction of a nonalcohol 
beer was not surprising in view of an antialcohol atmosphere he 
said prevailed in the united states 
steinman said nonalcoholic beers had not proven widely popular 
in the united states largely because they lacked the taste of 
regular beer and because brewers had found it difficult to brew a 
nonalcohol beer with real beer taste 
krishock said most brewers produced a nonalcoholic product by 
using a normal brewing cycle and then removing the alcohol along 
with the real beer taste 
under millers new brewing process when the yeast is added to 
the wort the end product of the barleycooking process the 
temperature is kept low so that fermentation is slow and produces 
minimal alcohol at the same time that the yeast contributes its 
taste to the brew 
miller said its super bowl ad campaign which will begin nov 5 
will feature 12 weeks of television radio and print advertising 
and a consumer sweepstakes offering expensepaid trips to super 
bowl xxiv in new orleans 
the celebrity teams will be coached by pro football hall of 
famer larry csonka and actor george wendt of televisions 
cheers while actor richard moll of televisions night 
court will referee 
